Philippine Stocks: MacroAsia, Racing Club, Rizal, Semirara

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-03-09T04:31:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/philippine-stocks-macroasia-racing-club-rizal-semirara.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses, and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.7 percent to
3,926.86, the highest close since Jan. 28.    MacroAsia Corp. (MAC)  , a provider of in-flight catering
services, jumped 7.3 percent to 3.38 pesos, the biggest gain
since Oct. 8. The company bought back 45,000 of its own shares
at 3.05 pesos each, a stock exchange filing showed.    Philippine Racing Club (PRC)  Inc, a horse racetrack
operator, increased 7.2 percent to 5.79 pesos, the most since
Feb. 18. Sta. Lucia Land Inc. (SLI PM) said it bought a 12.09
percent stake in the company for 298 million pesos. Sta. Lucia
gained 1.7 percent to 1.17 pesos, the most since Feb. 25.    Rizal Commercial Banking Corp. (RCB)   increased 3.2
percent to 27.50 pesos, the sharpest gain since Feb. 2. The
Philippine central bank approved the lender’s plan to sell 73.45
million shares to International Finance Corp., a stock exchange
filing showed. Rizal Bank didn’t state the price of the sale.    Semirara Mining Corp. (SCC)  , the largest coal producer,
advanced 3.6 percent to 222 pesos, the highest close based on
prices going back to March 1999. Semirara confirmed a report
that its owner is in talks with a Chinese group for a nickel
smelting plant venture that will be located in the economic zone
it’s building.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
